cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.MA 

The paper presents a new algorithm for reinforcement learning that provides probabilistic out-of-sample safety guarantees during online learning. This involves leveraging Wasserstein ambiguity sets to create a hierarchy of machines within the constrained Markov decision process (CMDP). Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following sub-categories: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning)
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence)
- cs.RO (Robotics)
- cs.SY (Systems and Control)
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems)
